4. Theoretical Risk Management

Risk is managed by making all assumptions explicit and linking them to theorems.

Definition 4.1 (Formal Risk).
A formal risk is a statement of the form “if assumption A holds, then property P is guaranteed”. The assumption A is a mathematical condition on the model (e.g., bounds on sensor noise, environment parameters). The property P is a safety invariant.

Risk Register (Symbolic).

Risk ID Failure Mode Formal Guarantee Assumptions Residual Risk
