7. Conclusion

We have presented the mathematical foundations and architectural design of the Neuromorphic Somatic‑Meta Architecture (NSMA) and its instantiation for the E4 platform. The framework unifies embodiment, perception, and cognition through differential geometry, information geometry, sheaf theory, control barrier functions, and homotopy type theory. The layered architecture provides formal interfaces and a verification chain that preserves safety properties. This theoretical work establishes a rigorous basis for future research in embodied autonomous safety.

